H0.text: One hundred thousand is the best estimate for the number of stars in the Milky Way Galaxy.

H1.text: One hundred million is the best estimate for the number of stars in the Milky Way Galaxy.

H2.text: One hundred billion is the best estimate of the number of stars in the Milky Way Galaxy.

H3.text: One hundred trillion is the best estimate for the number of stars in the Milky Way Galaxy.

A4.text: The Milky Way contains between 100 and 400 billion stars and at least that many planets.
